<div id="review_173770130" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/173770130" />
    <a title="Chris" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2238411-chris"><img alt="Chris" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/173770130?book_show_action=true">Jun 04, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chris" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chris" href="/user/show/2238411-chris">Chris</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780554305271" href="/book/show/10850427-the-vita-merlini">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2238411-chris?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2238411-chris?shelf=mythology-and-fairy-tales">mythology-and-fairy-tales</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer173770130" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7452299416092586296">Well, this is definitely a nerds book. Only a die hard King Arthur fan would wish to read the original texts written by the famed Geoffery of Monmouth. although not as romanticized as many other works, or as storylike/historical as his History of the Kings of Brittan, this work was nevertheless enjoyable. The similarities to Classic poetry, such as the introduction and the catalogs, were especially noticeable. The prophecies were harder to follow and required consulting the notes at the back of </span>
  <span id="freeText7452299416092586296" style="display:none">Well, this is definitely a nerds book. Only a die hard King Arthur fan would wish to read the original texts written by the famed Geoffery of Monmouth. although not as romanticized as many other works, or as storylike/historical as his History of the Kings of Brittan, this work was nevertheless enjoyable. The similarities to Classic poetry, such as the introduction and the catalogs, were especially noticeable. The prophecies were harder to follow and required consulting the notes at the back of the book, as is expected, and at time the narrative dragged. But the highlight, for me, was definitely the section relating the rise of Vortinger, the death of Aurelius Ambrosius, the Coronation of Arthur, and, sadly, the Battle of Camalan- essentially the classic cannon. On the whole an interesting read and an excellent addition to any mythological, or Arthurian, library.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7452299416092586296" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


